event on editable text controls in your app.","pos":[12985,13174],"source":" You can provide custom handling of the [Paste](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/xaml/windows.ui.xaml.controls.textbox.paste.aspx) event on editable text controls in your app."},{"content":"For example, you might remove the line breaks from a multi-line address when pasting it into a single-line search box.","pos":[13175,13293]},{"content":"Or, you might check the length of the pasted text and warn the user if it exceeds the maximum length that can be saved to a database.","pos":[13294,13427]},{"content":"For more info and examples, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Paste<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/xaml/windows.ui.xaml.controls.textbox.paste.aspx)</ept> event.","pos":[13428,13576],"source":" For more info and examples, see the [Paste](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/xaml/windows.ui.xaml.controls.textbox.paste.aspx) event."},{"content":"Here, we have an example of these properties and methods in use.","pos":[13578,13642]},{"content":"When you select text in the first text box, the selected text is displayed in the second text box, which is read-only.","pos":[13643,13761]},{"content":"The values of the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>SelectionLength<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/xaml/windows.ui.xaml.controls.textbox.selectionlength.aspx)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>SelectionStart<ept id=\"p2\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/xaml/windows.ui.xaml.controls.textbox.selectionstart.aspx)</ept> properties are shown in two text blocks.","pos":[13762,14074],"source":" The values of the [SelectionLength](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/xaml/windows.ui.xaml.controls.textbox.selectionlength.aspx) and [SelectionStart](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/xaml/windows.ui.xaml.controls.textbox.selectionstart.aspx) properties are shown in two text blocks."},{"content":"This